"a.终年的；永久的 【英】 adj. 终年的(present all the year)；永久的(perpetual, enduring) 【考】 反义词：fleeting(飞 逝的) 【记】 per＋enn(年)＋ial→ 一年到头的→永久的 【例】 Tom prefers perennial plants to those that last only a single year. adj. 终年永久的 = enduring; 四季常青的 【记】per所有, enn年, ial－一年中的所有的－永久的pe破, ren人, nial: 小人活千年, 破人活万年－永久的 【反】fleeting(adj 飞逝的; 短暂的) 【记】per 全部 + ennial 年 【相关】annual 一年的， perennial (adj.)  1640s, ""evergreen,"" formed in English from Latin perennis ""lasting through the year (or years),"" from per- ""through"" (see per) + annus ""year"" (see annual). Botanical sense of ""Remaining alive through a number of years"" is attested from 1670s; figurative meaning of ""enduring, permanent"" is from 1750. Related: Perennially. For vowel change, see biennial. The noun meaning ""a perennial plant"" is from 1763."
